# AI Instructions

CRITICAL RULE: This project STRICTLY uses Docker for all development, testing, compiling, and building.

DO NOT run `cargo`, `npm`, `node`, `wrangler`, or any other build/test tools directly on the host machine.
ALL commands must be executed inside the Docker container. 

You must first ensure the container is running globally:
`docker-compose up -d`

Then, execute commands inside the container using `docker-compose exec dev <command>`, or enter the shell using `docker-compose exec dev bash`.

For example, to build the CLI:
`docker-compose exec dev bash -c "cd packages/cli && cargo build --release"`

To run tests:
`docker-compose exec dev bash -c "cd packages/key-server && cargo test"`
